To determine the percentage of the astronaut's weight on Venus relative to Earth, use the formula:  
\[
\text{Percentage} = \left( \frac{\text{Weight on Venus}}{\text{Weight on Earth}} \right) \times 100
\]  
Substituting the given values:  
\[
\text{Percentage} = \left( \frac{182}{211} \right) \times 100 \approx 86.2\%
\]  
The closest option provided is **86%** (Option D).  

Answer: D
